cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on vision-based control of real-world robots and collision avoidance tasks using a quadrotor.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of deep reinforcement learning for the task.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is relevant as the quadrotor uses a monocular camera for collision avoidance.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of a hybrid approach combining real-world and simulated data for training the model.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also relevant as the paper discusses the dynamics of the quadrotor system and its control.
